					siglaPunto: "EX-LE-16",
					NomePunto: "36.EX. Xiyan (Knee Eyes)",
					AzioniPunto: "<p><b>T.C.M.</b><br> According to traditional Chinese medicine, Xiyan acupuncture points are very important for treating knee disorders.</p><p><b>Actions</b><br><span>•</span> Eliminates wind dampness<br><span>•</span> Reduces swelling<br><span>•</span> Relieves pain</p><p><b>Applications</b><br><span>•</span> Knee pain<br><span>•</span> Weakness of the lower limbs</p><p><b>Needle</b><br><span>•</span> Medial knee eye: 0.5-1 cun vertically or obliquely towards the lateral knee eye<br><span>•</span> Lateral knee eye: 0.5-1 cun vertically or obliquely towards the medial knee eye</p><p><b>Location</b><br>This point is best located with the patient's knee flexed (use knee support). The knee eyes can be positioned at the level of the lower margin of the patella, lateral and medial to the patellar ligament. The lateral knee eye corresponds to [.35.ST.] (Dubi), and the medial knee eye corresponds to [.36.EX.] (Neixiyan). Together, these two points form the extra point [.36.EX.] (Xiyan).</p><p><b>Precautions</b><br>Do not puncture too deeply to avoid intra-articular puncture (these points correspond to the incision sites for knee arthroscopy).</p>",
