					siglaPunto: "EX-LE-27",
					NomePunto: "38.EX. Heding (Crane Vertex)",
					AzioniPunto: "<p><b>T.C.M.</b><br> According to traditional Chinese medicine, Heding is an important point for treating knee joint pain.</p><p><b>Actions</b><br><span>•</span> Moves Qi and blood<br><span>•</span> Strengthens the knee joint</p><p><b>Applications</b><br><span>•</span> Good point for knee pain<br><span>•</span> Weakness of the leg and foot<br><span>•</span> Knee osteoarthritis<br><span>•</span> Beriberi</p><p><b>Needle</b><br>Insert the needle vertically 0.5-0.8 cun</p><p><b>Location</b><br>Slightly flex the patient's knee and support it with a knee rest. In the depression of the midpoint of the upper margin of the patella, you will find EX-LE-27 (Heding).</p>",
					ChiaviPunto: ""
